# Writing Standards

## Voice and audience

Graduate-level CS 6250 students preparing for exams. Clear and rigorous — not dumbed down unless editing a plain-language guide.

- Define jargon on first use; **bold** key terms.
- Prefer short paragraphs and tables over walls of text.
- Use analogies sparingly in full guides; freely in plain-language guides.

## Markdown conventions

```markdown
# H1 — page title only (one per file)

## H2 — major sections

### H3 — subsections

---   ← horizontal rule between major sections

| Column | Column |   ← tables for comparisons, milestones, device layers
```

**Admonitions** (Material for MkDocs):

```markdown
!!! tip "Exam prep"       ← sibling links to plain-language / quick study / quiz
!!! tip "Memory aid"      ← short mnemonic
!!! warning "Exam point"  ← common mistake
!!! info "Reference"      ← external citation
!!! abstract "Takeaway"   ← section summary
??? success "Answer"      ← hidden answer (practice-questions.md)
```

**Code and diagrams:**

- Fenced code blocks for pseudocode and packet layouts
- ` ```mermaid ` for topology/flow (see `docs/lesson-03/intradomain-routing.md`)
- Math via `$...$` or `$$...$$` (MathJax loaded in `mkdocs.yml`)

## Images

- Path: `images/lesson-NN/kebab-case-description.png` (relative to `docs/`; `NN` matches the lesson that owns the diagram)
- Alt text must describe the diagram, not the filename
- After adding an image file, reference it from the relevant lesson in the same edit

## What NOT to do

- Do not use `#` headings deeper than `###` unless the section truly needs it
- Do not use HTML `<details>` when `??? success` admonitions work
- Do not duplicate full lesson prose into plain-language guides — summarize and link to the full guide
- Do not paste unsourced claims; cite Canvas readings or Kurose & Ross when the full guide does
- Do not change `site_name`, theme palette, or plugin config in `mkdocs.yml` unless asked
- Do not add npm/node dependencies — this is a Python/MkDocs project only

## Terminology (use consistently)

| Prefer | Avoid |
|--------|-------|
| Autonomous System (AS) | "autonomous system" without caps on first mention |
| IGP / BGP | mixing "routing protocol" when the distinction matters |
| intradomain / interdomain | "internal/external routing" without context |
| end-to-end principle | "E2E" without defining it |
| segment / datagram / frame | "packet" when the layer-specific name matters |

Full cross-lesson term rules: see agent rule **terminology-consistency** when editing multiple lessons.
